.\" Manpage for Simple Shell.
.TH "Simple Shell" 1 "11 May 2022" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
Welcome to the Simple Shell project! The Simple Shell is a minimalistic Unix-like command-line interface. This program can be compiled and executed from the command line on various Linux distributions.

.SH OVERVIEW
The Simple Shell project is a collaborative effort led by Otung Princess and Akinpelu Faith, students at ALX School.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The Simple Shell returns the exit status of the last executed command. Additionally, it can exit when Ctrl-D is pressed or when the "exit" command is issued.

.SH SYNTAX
The syntax for using the Simple Shell is as follows:

.B Shell$ <command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...

To execute a command using the shell, you can simply type the command followed by its arguments.

.PP
.B $ <command> | ./hsh

You can also use a pipe (|) to send the output of one command as input to the Simple Shell.

.PP
EXAMPLES:

.B Shell$ /bin/ls
.PP
.B Shell$ ls -l
.PP
.B Shell$ cat textfile
.PP
.B $ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS
The Simple Shell supports the following built-in commands:

.SS env
List the current environment variables.

.SS exit
Exit the shell.

.SH SEE ALSO
.DASH(1)

.SH BUGS
There are currently no known bugs in the Simple Shell.

.SH AUTHOR
The Simple Shell project is led by Otung Princess and Akinpelu Faith as part of their coursework at ALX School.

.SH REPORTING BUGS
Please report bugs to the project team for prompt resolution.

